cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.LG

This paper deals with a security mechanism for software systems, specifically libraries, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also involves the optimization of runtime systems, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a demand-driven loading approach, which could be relevant to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category. The paper also deals with the reduction of ROP gadgets, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of decision trees, which could be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
